<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOKSTORE SURVIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was with some surprise that I read about the demise of Eric Chaim Kline, 
Bookseller in Stephen Games' Oct. 16 commentary, "Superstores, Narrowed 
Choices," which reviews the impact of superstores on the Los Angeles book 
scene. 
</P>
<P>
 To set the record straight, my store at 1343 4th St. in Santa Monica was 
destroyed by the Jan. 17 Los Angeles earthquake and not by the competition of 
the superstores. Within two weeks of the quake we were operating out of an 
office -- now moved to LAX -- and have been available by appointment, filling 
special orders, responding to our clients' needs, and reachable by phone at our 
old number, which is still listed and in force. 
</P>
<P>
 ERIC CHAIM KLINE 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 
</P>
