QUAKE ROCKS PHILIPPINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A strong earthquake rocked the Philippine island of Mindoro early today, 
killing at least three people and destroying some homes. 
</P>
<P>
 The quake had a preliminary magnitude of 6.7 and was centered in a strait six 
miles north of Calapan, a town on the northern end of the island, said the 
Philippine Institute of Vulcanology and Seismology. 
</P>
<P>
 It was felt throughout the central and south Philippines, including Manila. 
</P>
