<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; USC; ANKLE INJURY DOESN'T SLOW ROB JOHNSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC emerged from its 45-28 victory over Arizona on Saturday with no major 
injuries. Quarterback Rob Johnson, who re-injured his sprained right ankle in 
the fourth quarter and didn't return to the game, was walking without a limp 
afterward and will play Saturday against UCLA.Freshman starting guard Phalen 
Pounds, who has missed six games after an arthroscopic knee procedure, is 
listed as probable for UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 USC-UCLA history: The last five USC-UCLA games have been decided by a total of 
13 points. . . . UCLA has won the last three games, but USC leads in the 
series, which dates to 1929, 34-22-7. . . . In games in the Rose Bowl, UCLA is 
ahead 4-2, but USC has won two of the last three there. . . . In the last game 
at the Rose Bowl, in 1992, a two-point USC conversion try with 41 seconds left 
failed and UCLA won, 38-37. . . . Of the 63 games in the series, 34 have had 
the Rose Bowl on the line for at least one team and USC leads in those games, 
21-11-2. When the Rose Bowl has been on the line for only USC, the Trojans are 
3-0-1. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
