<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ON-LINE COMPUTER NETWORK SEEKS FEEDBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Business Resource Center for Ventura County, an on-line computer network 
designed to promote economic growth in the county, is seeking suggestions about 
what kind of information it should provide. 
</P>
<P>
 Thus far, the center has compiled information about the county's economic 
development associations, chambers of commerce, business assistance programs, 
professional societies and service clubs. 
</P>
<P>
 A community calendar is also being developed, and an on-line literacy program 
is planned. 
</P>
<P>
 Access to the service is free. Information: (805) 658-7462. 
</P>
