</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two faculty members of the pathology department at the University of Michigan 
Medical School have been named to positions at Camarillo-based BioSource 
International Inc., a supplier of biomedical research test kits. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Jones, an instructor and researcher, has joined BioSource as its vice 
president of research and development.He will supervise an expanded program 
that will concentrate on production of the basic components in the firm's 
product lines and the identification of potential new products. 
</P>
<P>
 He has been an instructor in immunology, immunochemistry, molecular biology 
and biomedical research techniques, and has been a consultant to NASA and 
private corporations. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Ward, a professor and chairman of Michigan's pathology department, will 
serve on BioSource's scientific advisory board. He has been a consultant to 
various commercial and government research organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Yoshihide Hagiwara, founder of Oxnard-based Green Foods Corp., is a recipient 
of Japan's Drug and Medical Meritorious Service Award for 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 The award is in recognition of Hagiwara's extraction techniques that allow 
nutrients to be stabilized and retained during the powderizing of raw 
vegetables and Chinese herbs. 
</P>
