REGIONAL ROUNDUP: PORT HUENEME CHAMBER SUPPORTS BRAC '95 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Port Hueneme Chamber of Commerce has voted to support Brac '95, a task 
force formed to keep Navy installations in Ventura County.But the chamber's 
directors stopped short of making a financial contribution to the effort. 
</P>
<P>
 A contribution isn't possible at this time, chamber directors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brac '95 is made up of defense contractors, government officials and others 
who are concerned about the potential impact of closing the bases at Hueneme 
and Point Mugu. 
</P>
<P>
 The group says the endangered bases provide thousands of jobs and pump more 
than $1 billion annually into Ventura County's economy. 
</P>
