</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Ann Conway, ; Steve Kresal 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GETTING INSIDE: How much do you hate tobacco smoke? Enough to wear your 
clothes inside-out for a day? . . . . That's what the American Cancer Society 
wants from you on Thursday, for its annual "Great American Smoke-Out" day. It's 
seeking help from hundreds of local companies. Says spokeswoman Jennifer 
Guenette: "If what happens on your inside, happened on your outside, would you 
still smoke?" . . . . Will people really do this? Yes, she says, if they want 
to "lighten up instead of light up." 
</P>
<P>
 BOOMING MORNING: What happens in Southern California when your walls shake a 
little and you hear a booming noise? . . . . "I thought it was an earthquake," 
says Lettie Ajawara of Mission Viejo. This time it was something in the air, 
not in the ground. . . . Monday morning the space shuttle Atlantis landed at 
Edwards Air Force Base in the Mojave Desert -- instead of Florida as planned. 
The booming sound as it re-entered the earth's atmosphere about 7:30 a.m. could 
be heard throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
 MEGA-GIVERS: After years of generous giving -- in time and money -- by 
developer Charles Hester and his wife, Nora, of Corona del Mar, the thank-yous 
are rolling in. . . . Hoag Memorial Hospital Presbyterian this year honored 
them as the "Sweet Heart Couple" for their efforts. Now, in one week's span, 
they've been chosen honorary chair for events by both Chapman University and 
the Boys and Girls Clubs. Today the couple will be honored at a breakfast at 
the Hyatt Regency Irvine Hotel on National Philanthropy Day, by the local 
society of fund-raising executives. 
</P>
<P>
 FAMILIAR FACE? The Southern Section high school football playoffs usually 
offer local teams a chance to play unfamiliar opponents. But not in Division V 
this year -- all its 16 teams are from Orange County (Prep Extra, V1). . . . 
Top seeded is Sea View League champion Newport Harbor Sailors (10-0). No. 2 is 
the Savanna Rebels of Anaheim (8-2), the Orange League champion. 
</P>
