<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; BALL FIELD TO HONOR SLAIN POLICE OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Oxnard City Council today is expected to name a city softball field in 
honor of Police Officer James O'Brien, who was shot and killed last year while 
trying to stop the murderous rampage of Alan Winterbourne. 
</P>
<P>
 The newly renovated softball field at Beck Park at C and Kamala streets in 
south Oxnard, would be dedicated Nov. 22 in memory of the 10-year veteran, who 
was active in local boxing and karate programs for children. 
</P>
<P>
 "With all the things that Jim did with kids, it will be nice to know that his 
name will live on in a facility they use," Assistant Police Chief Tom Cady 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Winterbourne killed four people and injured three others during a shooting 
spree last December before being gunned down by Oxnard police outside a Ventura 
unemployment office. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
