<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; HMO SEEKS OK FOR MEDICAL BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to retain more doctors who practice family medicine, Foundation 
Health Inc. will ask the Camarillo Planning Commission tonight to approve its 
proposal to build a 19,120-square-foot building in eastern Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 The single-story building would include examining rooms, X-ray laboratories 
and a pharmacy, said company spokesman Kurt Davis.The building is proposed for 
a vacant three-acre parcel near Adolfo Road and Avenida Acaso. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis said that health maintenance organizations such as Foundation Health 
have recently found themselves vying with other organizations to retain general 
medical practitioners. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, about a dozen doctors under contract with the company run their 
practices out of their own facilities. 
</P>
<P>
 "Basically, we are offering our doctors a chance to work in a facility that 
would house all of their basic medical needs under one roof," Davis said. "They 
would be left alone to practice the art of medicine and not have to worry about 
the overhead." Davis said the project will cost the company an estimated $4 
million to $5 million and could be completed by June, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Foundation Health is the largest group health-care provider in Ventura County 
with more than 30,000 members. The company is currently considering plans to 
build similar-sized buildings in Ventura and Oxnard, Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Planning Commission will consider the application tonight at 7:30 at City 
Hall, 601 Carmen Drive. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
