<P>
OTHER DRIVER SUES RAVELING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On the day he announced his retirement from coaching because of injuries he 
suffered in an auto accident, George Raveling was sued Monday by the driver of 
the other car for allegedly running a red light. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Ziehm filed a personal-injury suit against Raveling, claiming he 
suffered head and neck injuries in the accident Sept. 25. Ziehm, a former 
employee at the USC School of Dentistry, seeks unspecified damages. 
</P>
