<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: FARROUX CHANGES HER MIND, SIGNS WITH NEVADA LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westminster's Amber Farroux signed a letter of intent Monday to play women's 
basketball at Nevada Las Vegas, 1 1/2 weeks after making an oral commitment to 
attend Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 Farroux, a forward, averaged nine points and seven rebounds last year. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought I wanted to go to Long Beach, and UNLV was still in the picture," 
Farroux said. "UNLV asked me to come on an unofficial visit on Friday and I 
liked it a lot. So I decided to sign with UNLV." 
</P>
<P>
 She said she preferred the UNLV campus, and its academic and basketball 
programs to Long Beach State. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
