<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL '94-'95: EMPIRE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CENTURY 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 12-12 3-7 02,12,18 COACH 
RECORD AT SCHOOL Jeff Watts 43-47 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P 
Addie Alexander So. 5-7 G Nina Alexander Sr. 5-9 F Rosa Palacios Sr. 5-7 F 
04,17,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Melissa Astran Jr. 5-5 G Ashliegh 
Griset Jr. 5-9 F Adriana Moreno Sr. 5-4 G 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. 
P Vicki Gordon Jr. 5-6 G Talia Love Fr. 6-2 C Yvette Martinez Fr. 5-5 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Entering a new league, the Centurions have an uphill climb to their fifth 
consecutive playoff appearance. Nina Alexander returns for her fourth year 
after averaging 14.7 points and 9.7 rebounds and being selected first-team 
All-Pacific Coast League last season. Watts hopes to move her to the off-guard 
position to take advantage of her outside shooting. She is joined by sister 
Addie Alexander, who averaged seven points and was an all-league honorable 
mention selection last year, and Palacios, the only other returning senior 
starter. Joining Addie in the backcourt is Moreno, who is back after suffering 
a knee injury that kept her sidelined all last season. Watts is relying on 
freshman newcomers Martinez and Love to contribute heavily from the outset. 
Both could break into the starting lineup, which would pose problems with 
inexperience early on. Palacios and Griset will help out in the post, which 
Watts expects to be one of the Centurions' biggest weaknesses because of the 
lack of height. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 November 26 vs. Santa Ana; 30-December 2 Century tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 December 6 at Laguna Hills; 8 vs. Sunny Hills; 15-17 at Orange Lutheran 
tournament; 27-29 at Laguna Beach tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 January 3 at Orange; 4 vs. Saddleback; 10 vs. Cypress; 12 vs. El Dorado; 17 at 
Kennedy; 19 at Loara; 24 vs. Katella; 26 vs. Kennedy; 31 at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 February 2 at Katella; 7 at El Dorado; 9 vs. Loara. 
</P>
