<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL '94-'95: EMPIRE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LOARA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 2-19 1-9 02,15,18 COACH 
RECORD AT SCHOOL Vicki Mallett 0-0 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P 
Paola Flores Jr. 5-7 G Ellen Hsu Sr. 5-5 G Becky Joosten Sr. 6-0 F 
04,17,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Carole Jackson Jr. 5-8 F Miriam 
Martinez Sr. 5-7 G 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Christina Colon Fr. 
5-10 G Ann Halsig So. 6-0 F Betsy Holman Fr. 5-8 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Mallett is hoping to return this program to its glory days. The Saxons have 
struggled the past couple years, including two-victory seasons each of the last 
two years. She inherits only three seniors and five returners from last year's 
fifth-place team, which won only one league game. The lack of depth means 
freshmen Colon and Holman will play a lot. Colon is one of the best freshmen in 
the league, and is expected to start from the outset. The Saxons will also 
struggle with rebounding and scoring in the post. Overall team quickness and a 
fast-break style offense should help the Saxons win more than a handful of 
games. Mallett says the team philosophy consists of outlasting opponents by 
being in better condition and compares the team strategy to Arkansas' "Thirty 
minutes of hell." Flores will move to point guard and, along with Hsu, will run 
the show. Joosten and Jackson will provide a majority of the scoring in the 
paint. Experience is definitely a strong point, with three seniors and two 
juniors returning. Mallett says the team's goal is to finish with a .500 
record. A tough summer regimen and a less-than demanding nonleague schedule 
make that possible. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 1 at Garden Grove; 6 vs. Buena Park; 8 vs. Santa Ana; 13 at Savanna; 
15 at Anaheim; 19 at Estancia; 22 vs. Mission Viejo; 27-30 at Marina 
tournament. 
</P>
