<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: HIGHLAND PARK; 
SKATEBOARD DEATH SPURS LAPD WARNING TO PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 9-year-old boy's death in a skateboard accident in Highland Park -- the 
second such accident in the area in recent weeks -- prompted police to remind 
parents Monday about the dangers of the sport.  
</P>
<P>
 Jezraeel Leodones was killed Sunday afternoon when he sat on his skateboard 
and rode down a 30-foot driveway into the path of a car, said Los Angeles 
Police Detective Loren Zimmerman of the Central Traffic Division. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second such accident in six weeks in the neighborhood, he said. A 
6-year-old boy was killed Sept. 30 when he sat down on his skateboard and raced 
out a driveway into the path of a car. 
</P>
<P>
 The earlier incident occurred about a mile from Sunday's accident in the 6100 
block of Springvale Drive, Zimmerman said. Neither motorist was cited.  
</P>
<P>
 "Parents should be cautioned that skateboarding, in itself, is dangerous even 
for adults," Zimmerman said. "Parents should not allow this activity by their 
children or on their property," the detective said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
