<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: REDONDO BEACH; WOMAN, 2 
SONS CHARGED IN ALLEGED STAGED ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman and her two sons, accused in the staged robbery of an armored truck in 
Redondo Beach, were each charged with five felony counts Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Arraigned in South Bay Municipal Court were Maria Aracely Rivera-Cordero, 49, 
and her son, Luis Fernando Roca, 31, both of La Puente, and Jorge Mario Roca, 
28. 
</P>
<P>
 Luis Roca and his mother are accused of being the gunman and getaway driver, 
respectively, in Wednesday's holdup in front of a Smith's Food King at 4001 
Marine Ave.  
</P>
<P>
 The younger Roca brother was the Brinks guard who was "robbed," prosecutors 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 The mother and Luis Rocawere were arrested minutes later after being chased by 
an officer who was in the parking lot at the time of the heist.  
</P>
<P>
 Luis Roca allegedly walked up behind his brother as a cash delivery was being 
made, grabbed the younger man's gun and fired several shots as he fled in the 
getaway car driven by his mother.  
</P>
<P>
 Jorge Roca was arrested the next day after he reportedly told his employer the 
identity of the robbery suspects.  
</P>
<P>
 The three are charged with one count each of conspiracy to commit robbery, 
robbery, grand theft, shooting at an occupied motor vehicle and willfully 
evading a law enforcement officer.  
</P>
<P>
 It also was alleged that the robbery involved more than $150,000 and that a 
handgun was used during the commission of the crime. Bail was recommended at 
$250,000 for each defendant. 
</P>
