<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: AGOURA HILLS; PARK SERVICE FILLS RECREATION AREA POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott E. Erickson, 46, has been appointed the new deputy superintendent of the 
Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area, the National Park Service has 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson, who will assume his new position Nov. 29, succeeds William Webb, who 
retired in May. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson's last job was safety and environmental health manager for Yosemite 
National Park. Prior to that he was marketing manager and consultant for a 
Boise, Ida., software company. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the break in his park service career, Erickson was chief ranger at 
Everglades National Park in Florida; program manager in the Washington branch 
of fire management in the Boise Interagency Fire Center, and fire management 
officer for BLM in Alaska. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson graduated from the University of Maryland with a major in economics. 
TIM MAY 
</P>
