<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WOODLAND HILLS; WARNER CENTER FIRMS FOCUS ON RECYCLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business and property owners in the Warner Center Assn. have pooled their 
recycling efforts, reducing their trash output by more than one-third over the 
last four years, leaders of the Woodland Hills group said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The closed-loop concept is taking your trash and recycling as much of it as 
possible and purchasing recycled goods as much as possible," said Brad 
Rosenheim, the association's executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first four months of this year, association members have reduced their 
trash by 43% compared to 1990, according to the association. 
</P>
<P>
 Plans include increasing purchases of recycled products and looking into 
gray-water issues, according to Rosenheim. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
