GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: LA CRESCENTA; ATHLETIC CLUB COLLECTS FOOD FOR 
HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A canned-food drive at the Foothill Athletic Club is wrapping up its final 
week to help a program that feeds the homeless in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 "We do this every year," said Rick Crews, manager of the club at 3831 Lowell 
Ave., La Crescenta. 
</P>
<P>
 The drive raises about 950 pounds of canned food each year. Club members and 
the general public drop off the cans in a bin just inside the club entrance. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's getting full already," said Crews. Members who bring in five cans or 
more can bring a guest to the club free. The monthlong drive ends Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The donated food is given to the LIFE organization, which stands for "Love Is 
Feeding Everyone," Crews said. 
</P>
<P>
 The food drive is in its fifth year. ED BOND 
