<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don't expect a dramatic building boom in Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is expected to see modest growth in the number of housing units over 
the next 25 years, according to estimates by the city's Planning Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Between 1995 and 2000, single-family homes and multiple-family dwellings will 
increase by just a little more than 500 units, based on a county projection. 
Currently, there are about 46,300 housing units in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 By 2020, officials estimate the city will have about 50,000 housing units. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove has a population of about 150,000. Today 
</P>
<P>
 The Corona del Mar Library will present a puppet show at 10:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Storyteller Barbara Klein will relate stories from around the world. The 
program, part of Children's Book Week, is aimed for youngsters in grades 1 
through 4. 
</P>
<P>
 The library is at 420 Marigold Ave. The show will be presented at 3 p.m. at 
the Mariners Library, 2005 Dover Drive in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the puppet shows, call (714) 717-3807. 
</P>
