<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED WHEN EJECTED FROM CAR IN FREEWAY WRECK; PASSENGER IS UNHURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman was killed Sunday night when her speeding car went out of control and 
plunged down a freeway embankment, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Coroner's officials identified the woman as Lupe Hernandez, 24, of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said she was thrown from the Toyota Corolla when it careened over the 
embankment, hit a tree and rolled over near the Riverside Freeway east of 
Lakeview Avenue. Hernandez was not wearing a seat belt, said CHP spokeswoman 
Officer Angel Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez was driving west at about 80 m.p.h. when she lost control, Johnson 
said. Police are investigating whether Hernandez was intoxicated, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
 A 13-year-old passenger, Valerie Salomon of Anaheim, was unhurt in the 9 p.m. 
crash. The girl, who was wearing a seat belt, is the sister of Hernandez's 
boyfriend, Johnson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
