Hills, QB; Brent Santoro, Esperanza, OL/DL; Chris Stretch, Esperanza, QB; Jerry 
Sprewell, Long Beach Poly, LB; Taeao Saluasa, Long Beach Poly, LB; Ryan 
Williams, Bellflower St. John Bosco, RB. 
</P>
<P>
 Best draw: Mater Dei. A clear field to the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Worst draw: Bishop Amat. The top-seeded team is looking at facing a rather 
nasty Edison team in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
 Notes: In case anyone out there doesn't know, Los Alamitos has a 45-game 
unbeaten streak. One more victory ties the Southern Section record held by 
Temple City (1969-73) and Canyon Country Canyon (1983-86) . . . The Griffins 
have won three consecutive section titles. No Orange County team has won four 
consecutive . . . Los Alamitos can complete a sweep of divisions. The Griffins 
began their title run in Division III in 1991, then won the Division II 
championship the last two seasons . . . Esperanza tied Los Alamitos, 14-14, in 
the 1992 Division title game . . . Mater Dei could play Eisenhower in the 
second round. The Monarchs were throttled, 56-3, by Eisenhower last season . . 
. McCutcheon, who has gained more than 1,741 yards and scored 25 touchdowns, is 
the son of former Ram Lawrence McCutcheon. Perry, an ever-dangerous receiver, 
is the son of former Ram Rod Perry. Their fathers were teammates in the late 
1970s . . . Bishop Amat opens against Mission Viejo, just as it did in 1992, 
when the Lancers won the title. 
</P>
