<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INFOMERCIAL PRODUCER DOUBLES ITS EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Positive Response Television Inc., a fast-growing infomercial producer, 
doubled its earnings in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sherman Oaks company said its net income was $916,000 in the three months 
ended Sept. 30, up from a $442,000 profit a year earlier. Its quarterly revenue 
surged to $10.6 million from $1.52 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the recent nine-month period, Positive Response earned $1.25 million, an 
89% gain from a $661,000 profit a year before. Revenue grew to $17.1 million 
from $2.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed its quick growth to the money it raised in its initial 
public stock offering in May, the success of its infomercials and its expanding 
business distributing infomercials developed by others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
