</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
123 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: DICK CLARK REPORTS DROP IN 1ST QUARTER REVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dick Clark Productions Inc., a Burbank-based television production company, 
reported a steep slide in earnings in its fiscal first quarter that ended Sept. 
30. 
</P>
<P>
 The company posted a $19,000 profit in the quarter, compared to year-earlier 
earnings of $431,000. Revenues fell 38% to $8.45 million, compared to revenues 
of $13.7 million in the first quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said the decline in revenue was due to a decrease in television 
production activity, and a decrease in the number of projects handled by the 
company's corporate events subsidiary. These losses were partially offset, the 
company said, by an increase in revenues and profits from the company's "Dick 
Clark's American Bandstand Grill" restaurant chain. 
</P>
