<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: BIOSOURCE'S PROFITS FOR 3RD QUARTER DECLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Consolidation and moving expenses diminished the third-quarter profit reported 
by BioSource International Inc., a Camarillo-based supplier of materials and 
test kits used in biomedical research. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported earnings of $85,664 in the quarter that ended Sept. 30, 
compared to a year-earlier profit of $218,702.Sales totaled $1.62 million in 
the third quarter, up 12% from $1.45 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The third quarter results reflected $160,000 in costs related to the 
consolidation of the company's operations at a new facility in Camarillo, where 
the company has been based since 1990. Manufacturing, research, shipping and 
warehouse activities were moved from a facility in Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 "All employees except sales staff are now in one location and our monthly 
facility lease costs have been cut in half," said James Chamberlain, chief 
executive of BioSource. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first nine months of the year, BioSource reported earnings of $411,604 
on sales of $4.87 million, compared to a year-earlier profit of $419,021 on 
revenue of $4.06 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
