REGIONAL EARNINGS: FORTUNE PETROLEUM REPORTS 3RD-QUARTER LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fortune Petroleum Corp., an Agoura Hills oil and gas exploration and 
production company, reported a loss of $308,000 in the third quarter that ended 
Sept. 30, compared to a year-earlier loss of $21,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenues in the third quarter tumbled 13% to $854,000 from $976,000 in the 
same three-month period of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first nine months of the year, Fortune posted a loss of $972,000 on 
$2.6 million in revenues, compared to a $97,000 loss on revenues of $1.94 
million a year earlier.  
</P>
<P>
 Fortune said the latest loss was due to lower natural gas prices and higher 
operating costs related to properties acquired by the company earlier this 
year. The nine-month loss also reflects a one-time charge of $225,000 to be 
paid over a two-year period to the company's former president, Dan E. Pasquini, 
who resigned on June 23. 
