VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: HOME BUYERS AVERAGE $46,000 DOWN PAYMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County home buyers came up with an average down payment of $46,000 
during the third quarter.That's 19% of the average selling price of $243,000 
during the period, Dataquick Information Systems reports. 
</P>
<P>
 In comparison, buyers in Orange County made the highest down payment among 
Southern California counties, averaging $52,000. Purchasers in San Bernardino 
County put down the least -- $14,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Among California cities, the highest average down payment was $370,000 in 
Beverly Hills. The lowest was $3,000 in Bakersfield. 
</P>
