<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL AND RESTAURANTS; HOTEL WILL OFFER A CHOICE OF GOURMET OR 
TRADITIONAL THANKSGIVING FEASTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dining opportunities will be bountiful at Orange County restaurants this 
Thanksgiving. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who don't want to cook or to be conventional either, Surf & Sand 
Hotel in Laguna Beach is offering not only the traditional feast but also a 
gourmet menu. 
</P>
<P>
 The hotel's Splashes restaurant will feature Thanksgiving specialties a la 
carte as well as a three-course dinner from noon to 10 p.m. Prices will range 
from $15 to $20 for adults, with a $12 "Tom Turkey Platter" for children 12 and 
younger. 
</P>
<P>
 The regular dinner will feature butternut squash soup, autumn greens, wild 
mushroom flan and roasted turkey with potatoes, chestnut bread stuffing, 
cranberry relish and giblet sauce. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Surf & Sand's Towers restaurant, the choices will be a bit more exotic 
for four-course holiday meal, served from 1:30 to 8 p.m. and priced from $35 to 
$40. The gourmet feast kicks off with wild mushroom bisque and sauteed crab 
cakes. 
</P>
<P>
 Entrees include roasted free range turkey with potato garlic puree, chestnut 
stuffing and giblet sauce; roasted prime rib of beef with potato pancakes; and 
sauteed Atlantic salmon with spinach and autumn squash with champagne sauce. 
</P>
