<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL AND RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Grand Reopening: Anaheim Plaza hosts its grand reopening at 9:30 a.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County's oldest shopping center was torn down last year to make way for 
a new collection of stores that includes Mervyn's, Comp USA, Old Navy Clothing 
Co. and Ross Dress for Less. The 400,000-square-foot retail center will add a 
Wal-Mart store early next year. 
</P>
<P>
 Payless ShoeSource and Kenny Rogers Roasters have both signed on at the 
shopping center, as has Ross Stores Inc. The off-price retailer is opening 18 
new locations this fall, bringing its store total to 277 in 18 states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
