<P>
 Comarco Inc.: The Yorba Linda provider of wireless communications products, 
engineering services, and facility management services said that profit for the 
third quarter ended Oct. 30 totaled $952,000, or 20 cents a share, up from 
$652,000, or 12 cents a share, for the comparable period a year ago.Revenue 
rose to $18.3 million from $16.5 million. For the first nine months of fiscal 
1995, profit increased 35% to $2.3 million, or 47 cents a share, from $1.7 
million, or 32 cents a share, for the like period a year ago. Revenue rose to 
$50 million from $49.1 million. 
