<P>
 Moorpark College forward Nick Foster, a Thousand Oaks High graduate, has 
signed a letter of intent to play basketball at Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick (6-foot-9) will be playing in the Big West Conference against his twin 
brother and current teammate, Paul, who signed last week with UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 "Nick is a great passer and shoots very well," Pacific Coach Bob Thomason said 
Monday. "He also runs the floor well for a big man and will help us at the 
power forward position." 
</P>
<P>
 Nick and Paul starred for Thousand Oaks High, then briefly attended the Air 
Force Academy last fall. They returned to Southern California last season, Paul 
playing at Moorpark and Nick redshirting at Ventura. Nick transferred to 
Moorpark this season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Raymond Rivera, a sophomore right-handed pitcher at Mission College, has 
signed a letter of intent to play baseball for former Cal Lutheran Coach Rich 
Hill at the University of San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 Rivera, a San Fernando High graduate, said he chose the Dons over San Jose 
State. Rivera was 12-3 with a 2.87 earned-run average at Mission last spring. 
JEFF FLETCHER 
